Tip cloud-repo-create-wall
  When runtime=cloud
  Say Do not try to create a NEW GitHub repo from this session. It has been attempted four ways and refused four ways: the built-in GitHub tools (App installation token); a PAT in the environment (blocked by the agent proxy before reaching GitHub); a GitHub MCP custom connector via Anthropic OAuth (loads and authenticates as the real user, but the connector is itself a GitHub App, so GitHub returns 403 "Resource not accessible by integration"); and the same connector with a user-registered OAuth App supplied in Advanced settings (claude.ai silently ignores the client id and re-authorizes through Anthropic's App anyway). There is no configuration fix from here. Create the repo from a local session, or delegate to a GitHub Actions workflow holding a real PAT in Actions secrets. Note what DOES work here: custom MCP connectors load and bypass the network allowlist, so deploys (Vercel) and other connector-backed actions are fine. Reachability problems go through connectors; permission problems go through delegation.
